    "## What do all of these trees look like?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "LAvLJVx4-NBT"
   },
   "source": [
    "Note that while generating the tree structures is fast, generating the diagrams can be very slow."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "6VIGQgGh9kZo",
    "outputId": "58d7057b-2ff5-47b5-f93c-538aa178db73"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<IPython.core.display.Image object>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 2,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from pptrees.AdderTree import AdderTree as tree\n",
    "from pptrees.util import catalan\n",
    "\n",
    "width = 6\n",
    "# Generate all trees of width 9\n",
    "list_of_trees=[]\n",
    "for a in range(catalan(width-1)):\n",
    "  t = tree(width, start_point = a)\n",
    "  list_of_trees.append(t)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Visualize the trees in GIF form\n",
    "from pptrees.util import display_gif as display_gif\n",
    "from IPython.display import Image\n",
    "\n",
    "Image(display_gif(list_of_trees))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "isS1p2zM-Wki"
   },
   "source": [
    "## How do I get the tree that I want?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "UkeA8wEi-jc1"
   },
   "source": [
    "The number of total possible trees is known. Thus it is possible to assign an integer ID to every possible structure.<br>\n",
    "The labeling I chose is based on an order that arose naturally.<br>\n",
    "*If you, reader, happen to know the name of this specific tree traversal, please contact me as I've so far been unable to find it in literature.*\n",
    "\n",
    "To get a desired structure, simply initialize it with its label."
   ]
  },

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "PnnU2polA8L7"
   },
   "source": [
    "This order begins and ends with slower, **O(n)**, structures. In the middle are better-balanced, **O(lg n)**. However, each of these possible structures has useful delay, power, or area characteristics when viewed as a part of the complete adder (forest) structure."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "LrCgNrIOCXDJ"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Okay, I have a tree. How do I make it faster?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "vaZRZ6azCd5L"
   },
   "source": [
    "**Theory**\n",
    "\n",
    "In general, for the tree to be faster, it must be more balanced.<br>\n",
    "Keep in mind, however, that the speed of each individual tree is greatly affected by the forest it is a part of.\n",
    "\n",
    "If every tree in a forest is left-balanced (more commonly known as \"complete\"), theoretically each of the individual trees will be very fast, but as part of the greater forest they will each incur a delay penalty due to a large amount of necessary routing tracks.\n",
    "\n",
    "If each tree in a forest is right-balanced, theoretically each of the individual trees will be very fast, but as part of the greater forest they will each incur a delay penalty due to a large amount of fan-out."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "KgLN2xJwDZXQ"
   },
   "source": [
    "**Application**\n",
    "\n",
    "The library supports four methods of transforming trees.\n",
    "\n",
    "*   left_rotate - Rotates a given node left\n",
    "*   right_rotate - Rotates a given node right\n",
    "*   left_shift - Shifts a given node left into another subtree; the equivalent of AVL trees' RL rotate, except this is a generalized RRRRRRRR...L rotate.\n",
    "*   right_shift - Shifts a given node right into another subtree; the equivalent of AVL trees' LR rotate, except this is a generalized LLLLLLLL...R rotate.\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "6Ww7kHmzCWzq",
    "outputId": "fef0590d-2cd6-4a86-9447-835d33b4b60b"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "There are 4862 possible trees of width 10\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<pptrees.AdderTree.AdderTree at 0x7f3979d7c250>"

     "execution_count": 32,

    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from pptrees.AdderTree import AdderTree as tree\n",
    "from pptrees.util import catalan\n",
    "\n",
    "width = 10\n",
    "# First, check the total number of structures\n",
    "print(\"There are {0} possible trees of width {1}\".format(catalan(width-1),width))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Start at some initial point\n",
    "t = tree(width, start_point = 209)\n",
    "t"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,

    "# Speed up the tree\n",

    "\n",
    "t.right_rotate(t.root[1][1][1][1][0])\n",
    "t.left_rotate(t.root[1][1][1][1])\n",
    "t"

    "# Balance the tree even more by using sparseness\n",
    "t = tree(width, start_point = 209)\n",

  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "Sa5Ge_EIGKuT"
   },
   "source": [
    "## Okay, now how do I make a tree more power-efficient? Or smaller?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "Q7s4MM31GSJR"
   },
   "source": [
    "**Theory**\n",
    "\n",
    "Both area and power consumption are determined primarily not by an individual tree, but rather by the forest it is a part of.\n",
    "\n",
    "Both area and power consumption fall with an increasing number of shared nodes between trees. That is why serial adders have smaller area than parallel ones, and why the Brent-Kung structure has smaller area than the Kogge-Stone one.\n",
    "\n",
    "In general, the further right-balanced a tree is, the more nodes it is able to share. This is however just a rule of thumb.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Application**\n",
    "\n",
    "See the following example."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "RQLiDhBxHGK5",
    "outputId": "fccdc39a-f3a5-4798-8e0e-bdb27bea7de1"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "There are 132 possible trees of width 7\n",
      "There are 42 possible trees of width 6\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Let's say we only want the 6th and 7th bit of a sum.\n",
    "\n",
    "from pptrees.AdderTree import AdderTree as tree\n",
    "from pptrees.util import catalan\n",
    "\n",
    "width_big = 7\n",
    "width_small = 6\n",
    "# First, check the total number of structures\n",
    "print(\"There are {0} possible trees of width {1}\".format(catalan(width_big-1),width_big))\n",
    "print(\"There are {0} possible trees of width {1}\".format(catalan(width_small-1),width_small))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Next, initialize two random trees\n",
    "t_big = tree(width_big, start_point = 72)\n",
    "t_small = tree(width_small, start_point = 12)"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "Note that these two trees have no nodes in common. Let's give them some."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "4ANi8aqeIYQ2",
    "outputId": "0d9d1f28-b645-4925-f65f-a3aca5bb5b20"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<pptrees.AdderTree.AdderTree at 0x7fa033fd60a0>"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 7,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "t_small = tree(width_small, start_point = 12)\n",
    "# Make the left-hand side of the trees similar\n",
    "t_small.right_rotate(t_small.root[1][0])\n",
    "t_small.right_shift(t_small.root[1][0][1])\n",
    "t_small"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "NPjZ6WZmIzSh"
   },
   "source": [
    "The two trees have gone from sharing 0 nodes, to sharing 2 nodes. Area and power consumption has been reduced.\n",
    "\n",
    "We can visualize the shared nodes by creating a make-shift forest and using its methods.\n",
    "\n",
    "The nodes that have been painted partially red in t_small are shared between the two trees. This is merely cosmetic, intended to serve as a visual indicator.\n",
    "\n",
    "Note that the equivalent nodes in t_big have not been painted red. This is intentional.<br>\n",
    "The red marks nodes that need not be implemented in hardware.<br>\n",
    "Shared nodes only need to be implemented in hardware once, but they still need to be implemented that one single time."
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "9K1e27IMOwLA"
   },
   "source": [
    "### How do I get the ID of a tree after I've modified it?"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "U3y816IUO6nZ"
   },
   "source": [
    "The \"rank\" method gets the ID of a tree, while the \"unrank\" method creates a tree given a certain ID"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "id": "a0PU0oAVOveO",
    "outputId": "cf4a36ee-4184-4c9e-fbfa-73b7af4629b4"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "There are 132 possible trees of width 7\n",
      "There are 42 possible trees of width 6\n",
      "The rank (ID) of the big tree is 70\n",
      "The rank (ID) of the small tree is 19\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Let's say we only want the 6th and 7th bit of a sum.\n",
    "\n",
    "from pptrees.AdderTree import AdderTree as tree\n",
    "from pptrees.util import catalan\n",
    "\n",
    "width_big = 7\n",
    "width_small = 6\n",
    "# First, check the total number of structures\n",
    "print(\"There are {0} possible trees of width {1}\".format(catalan(width_big-1),width_big))\n",
    "print(\"There are {0} possible trees of width {1}\".format(catalan(width_small-1),width_small))\n",
    "\n",
    "# Next, initialize two random trees\n",
    "t_big = tree(width_big, start_point = 72)\n",
    "t_small = tree(width_small, start_point = 12)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Make the right-hand side of the trees similar\n",
    "t_big.right_shift(t_big.root[0][0][1])\n",
    "\n",
    "# Make the left-hand side of the trees similar\n",
    "t_small.right_rotate(t_small.root[1][0])\n",
    "t_small.right_shift(t_small.root[1][0][1])\n",
    "# Reduce the height of t_small\n",
    "t_small.left_rotate(t_small.root[1])\n",
    "\n",
    "print(\"The rank (ID) of the big tree is {0}\".format(t_big.rank()))\n",
    "print(\"The rank (ID) of the small tree is {0}\".format(t_small.rank()))"
   ]
  },
